pkg_lib CHANGELOG
==================

- v1.0.7 | Apr 05 2026:
  [Fix] pkg_rclocal_remove: preserve file permissions (stat/chmod) after
      mktemp+mv atomic replace — prevents rc.local losing 755 executable bit
      on CentOS 6 and Slackware (P1-1)
  [Fix] pkg_config_set: escape shell metacharacters (\, ", $, `) in values
      to prevent code execution when config files are sourced as root (P2-1)
  [Fix] pkg_config_migrate_var: escape shell metacharacters in migrated values
      to prevent injection when single-quoted originals are written into
      double-quoted context (P2-1 extension)
  [Fix] pkg_cron_restore_schedule: extend BRE search escaping to include
      [, ], ^, $ metacharacters for correctness (P2-2)
  [Fix] pkg_sed_replace, pkg_man_install: split search/replacement escaping —
      BRE search now escapes .*[\^$, replacement escaping unchanged (P3-3)
  [Change] pkg_manifest_load: add ownership check (-O) before sourcing
      manifest file — defense-in-depth for untrusted file contexts (P3-1)
  [Change] pkg_rclocal_remove: use grep -F for fixed-string matching
      instead of regex — strictly more correct for service name patterns (P3-2)
  [Change] pkg_symlink: replace rm+ln with command ln -sf to reduce TOCTOU
      window and fix pre-existing bare ln coreutils violation (P3-4)
  [Change] pkg_config_get: document raw-reader semantics — AWK-based extractor
      returns literal file bytes, not shell-interpreted values
  [Change] CI: batsman workflow pin v1.0.3 → v1.4.0

- v1.0.6 | Mar 26 2026:
  [New] pkg_fhs_gen_manifest: build-time function to generate tab-separated
      symlink manifest from FHS registry for runtime verification
  [New] pkg_fhs_verify_farm: runtime function to verify symlink farm integrity,
      auto-repair broken/missing/wrong-target symlinks, report unrecoverable
      errors when FHS targets are missing

- v1.0.5 | Mar 23 2026:
  [Change] README: restructure for rfxn documentation convention floor compliance;
      centered flat-square badges, bold one-liner, copyright blockquote, numbered
      sections (## 1-8), exit codes table, ## License, ## Support

- v1.0.5 | Mar 16 2026:
  [Fix] pkg_config_merge: use temp file for AWK output to prevent data loss
      when output path equals new_conf path
  [Fix] pkg_config_migrate_var: escape sed metacharacters in migrated values
      to prevent output corruption with &, |, /, \ characters
  [Fix] pkg_config_migrate_var: validate old_var and new_var as safe shell
      identifiers before use in grep/sed patterns
  [Fix] pkg_config_get: validate var name as safe shell identifier before
      use in grep pattern
  [Fix] pkg_backup, pkg_rclocal_remove: replace bare mv with command mv
      for alias-bypass portability
  [Change] pkg_config_get: remove dead AWK variable assignment
  [Fix] README: update version badge from 1.0.2 to 1.0.5
  [Fix] README: correct pkg_uninstall_man signature to section name
  [Fix] README: correct pkg_service_uninstall_multi signature to name suffixes
  [Change] README: annotate config merge examples as safe for in-place use
  [Fix] Replace bare rm with command rm across all 33 call sites for
      alias-bypass portability (class-wide fix per QA-002)

- v1.0.4 | Mar 15 2026:
  [Fix] pkg_config_set: validate $var as safe shell variable name
      [a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]* to prevent regex/sed injection via
      crafted variable names
  [Fix] pkg_man_install: escape $old_str and $new_str in sed replacement
      pairs using same pattern as pkg_sed_replace (handle &, |, /, \)

- v1.0.3 | Mar 14 2026:
  [New] pkg_config_merge: preserve permissions of template file on output;
      uses stat -Lc (GNU) with stat -Lf (FreeBSD) fallback chain;
      dereferences symlinks to get target permissions

- v1.0.2 | Mar 07 2026:
  [Fix] Replace hardcoded /usr/bin/cp with portable `command cp` across all 14
      call sites; fixes failures on CentOS 6 and Ubuntu 12.04 where cp lives
      at /bin/cp (no usr-merge)
  [Change] README: add consumer project links and CI badges

- v1.0.1 | Mar 07 2026:
  [New] README: add integration guide with install.sh/uninstall.sh boilerplate
      templates, config migration pattern, and consumer project references
  [New] README: add use cases section covering fresh install, upgrade with
      backup, multi-service install, FHS layout with symlink farm, and package
      generation workflows with code snippets
  [New] README: add troubleshooting section covering backup collision, service
      not starting, OS detection issues, symlink farm, config merge, and
      CentOS 6 known issues
  [Fix] pkg_sed_replace: escape | delimiter in old_path and new_path arguments
      before sed substitution, matching the escaping pattern from pkg_config_set
  [Change] pkg_backup_prune: replace ls -1 directory enumeration with find
      -maxdepth 1 -mindepth 1 -printf for robustness consistency
  [Change] pkg_set_perms: add inline comments on find 2>/dev/null suppressions
      per coding standards (best-effort traversal errors safe to ignore)
  [Change] pkg_service_enable, pkg_service_disable: add inline comments on
      systemctl 2>/dev/null suppressions (may fail if unit missing)

- v1.0.0 | Mar 06 2026:
  [New] pkg_lib.sh — shared packaging, install, and uninstall library for rfxn
      projects (3200+ lines, 80+ functions); zero project-specific code, all
      behavior controlled via PKG_* environment variables, bash 4.1+ compatible
  [New] Output functions: pkg_header, pkg_info, pkg_warn, pkg_error, pkg_success,
      pkg_section, pkg_item with terminal color detection (_pkg_color_init)
  [New] OS/platform detection: pkg_detect_os with /etc/os-release and legacy
      fallback chain (redhat-release, debian_version, gentoo, slackware, uname);
      pkg_detect_init (systemd/SysV/upstart/rc.local cascade);
      pkg_detect_pkgmgr (dnf/yum/apt/emerge/pkg/slackpkg via command -v);
      pkg_is_systemd, pkg_os_family accessors; all cached after first call
  [New] Dependency checking: pkg_check_dep with required/recommended/optional
      levels; pkg_check_deps for batch parallel-array checking; pkg_dep_hint
      for package-manager-specific install hints
  [New] Backup & restore: pkg_backup with copy/move methods, DDMMYYYY-EPOCH
      timestamps, collision-safe -N suffixes, configurable .bk.last symlink;
      pkg_backup_exists, pkg_backup_path for symlink queries;
      pkg_backup_prune for age-based cleanup with .bk.last protection;
      pkg_restore_files for selective glob-based restore;
      pkg_restore_dir for full subdirectory restore
  [New] File operations: pkg_copy_tree (recursive copy with attribute preservation),
      pkg_set_perms (dirs/files/executables), pkg_create_dirs (mkdir -p + chmod);
      pkg_symlink (create/update), pkg_symlink_cleanup (safe removal);
      pkg_sed_replace (sed -i with | delimiter across files),
      pkg_tmpfile (mktemp wrapper with PKG_TMPDIR support)
  [New] Service lifecycle: unified service management primitives normalizing
      systemd/SysV/Gentoo/Slackware init system handling across OS families;
      pkg_service_install/uninstall (unit/init script with auto-detection);
      pkg_service_install_timer, pkg_service_install_multi,
      pkg_service_uninstall_multi for multi-unit service bundles;
      pkg_service_start/stop/restart via shared _pkg_service_ctl cascade;
      pkg_service_enable with OS-family cascade (systemd/chkconfig/update-rc.d/
      rc-update/Slackware S-links), pkg_service_disable, pkg_service_exists,
      pkg_service_is_enabled; pkg_rclocal_add (idempotent), pkg_rclocal_remove;
      FreeBSD early-return guards on all service functions
  [New] Cron management: pkg_cron_install (auto-detect mode 644/755 from
      destination path), pkg_cron_remove, pkg_cron_cleanup_legacy (glob-based);
      pkg_cron_preserve_schedule (capture 5-field schedule with eval validation),
      pkg_cron_restore_schedule (restore with sed * escaping);
      _pkg_cron_read_schedule shared helper for deduplication
  [New] Documentation installation: pkg_man_install (copy + optional sed pairs +
      gzip + install to auto-detected man dir via _pkg_man_dir helper),
      pkg_bash_completion, pkg_logrotate_install (via shared _pkg_install_sysfile
      helper), pkg_doc_install (README/CHANGELOG/LICENSE to doc dir)
  [New] Config migration: pkg_config_merge (AWK two-pass merge preserving old
      values into new template), pkg_config_migrate_var (rename variable with
      optional upper/lower transform), pkg_config_clamp (clamp numeric config
      value to maximum with warning); pkg_config_get (AWK single-pass value
      extraction with quote stripping), pkg_config_set (sed-based in-place
      update or append, pipe-char safe)
  [New] FHS layout: pkg_fhs_register (parallel indexed array registry for
      src/dest/mode/type file mappings), pkg_fhs_install (install registered
      files with directory creation and permissions, failure counting);
      pkg_fhs_symlink_farm (backward-compat symlinks from legacy to FHS paths),
      pkg_fhs_symlink_farm_cleanup (remove symlinks and empty directories);
      pkg_fhs_gen_rpm_files (RPM %files with %config(noreplace) and %dir dedup),
      pkg_fhs_gen_deb_dirs, pkg_fhs_gen_deb_links, pkg_fhs_gen_deb_conffiles,
      pkg_fhs_gen_sed_pairs (sed expressions for path transformation)
  [New] Uninstall primitives: pkg_uninstall_confirm (interactive y/N prompt),
      pkg_uninstall_files (files/dirs with silent skip for missing),
      pkg_uninstall_man (multi-location man page removal),
      pkg_uninstall_cron, pkg_uninstall_logrotate, pkg_uninstall_completion,
      pkg_uninstall_sysconfig (RHEL + Debian paths)
  [New] Manifest support: pkg_manifest_load (source manifest file),
      pkg_manifest_validate (check PKG_NAME/VERSION/SUMMARY/INSTALL_PATH)
  [New] pkg_gen.sh — manifest-driven packaging artifact generator: reads
      pkg.manifest and templates, performs @@PLACEHOLDER@@ substitution,
      handles conditional blocks (@@IF_*@@/@@ENDIF_*@@) for feature flags,
      produces project-specific RPM spec, DEB debian/, Docker, Makefile,
      GHA workflow, and test artifacts; two-level token model for project
      customization; pipe-char safe sed escaping
  [New] Packaging templates: RPM spec (project.spec.in), DEB debian/ (control,
      rules, conffiles, dirs, links, preinst, postinst, postrm, changelog,
      copyright, source/format), Docker build/test Dockerfiles (el7, el9,
      deb), Makefile (tarball + native + Docker builds), GHA release workflow,
      package install verification script — all with @@PLACEHOLDER@@ tokens
  [New] README.md with library overview, quick-start examples, full function
      reference, pkg_gen.sh usage, manifest format, and template inventory
  [New] Test suite: 454 tests across 14 files covering all library sections;
      9-OS Docker test matrix (debian12, centos6-rocky10, ubuntu 12.04-24.04);
      CI workflow with lint + batsman reusable test workflow
  [Fix] Test assertions: replaced bare `! grep -q` with `run grep -q` +
      status check for proper BATS error handling (QA-001)
  [Fix] pkg_gen.sh: escape pipe character in sed substitution values to prevent
      breakage when manifest values contain | (QA-004)
  [Fix] pkg_gen.sh: removed dead _gen_warn() function (QA-002)
  [Fix] pkg_gen.sh: corrected misleading awk comment in conditional block
      cleanup to match actual behavior (QA-003)
